                <head>127. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (<gloss
                        target="#t_OECD1">OECD</gloss>) held its first Ministerial Meeting in Paris
                    November 16-17, 1961. Proposals by <persName corresp="#p_TJW2">John W.
                        Tuthill</persName>, Ambassador-designate to the <gloss target="#t_OECD1"
                        >OECD</gloss>, for U.S. initiatives at this upcoming <gloss
                        target="#t_OECD1">OECD</gloss> meeting emphasizing the recent dramatic
                    growth of the Western European nations and promoting a vigorous plan for future
                    cooperative economic development are contained in Cedto 295 from Paris, October
                    27, which is attached to a November 1 memorandum from <persName
                        corresp="#p_MER1">Edward R. Murrow</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_BMG2"
                        >McGeorge Bundy</persName>, endorsing and elaborating on <persName
                        corresp="#p_TJW2">Tuthill</persName>’s proposals. (<persName
                        corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName> Library, National Security Files,
                    Departments and Agencies Series, Department of State, 11/1/61-11/5/61) Under
                    Secretary of State for Economic Affairs <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">George W.
                        Ball</persName> headed the U.S. Delegation to this <gloss target="#t_OECD1"
                        >OECD</gloss> Ministerial Meeting. For text of his statement at the November
                    16 session, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, December
                    18, 1961, pages 1014-1018. For text of the communique, November 17, see ibid.,
                    December 18, 1961, pages 1018-1020. Documentation on the <gloss
                        target="#t_OECD1">OECD</gloss> Ministerial Meeting is in Department of
                    State, Central File 374.800.</p>
            </div>
